2019-03-07 13:17:19-05:00,11 Strategies for IRA Withdrawals,"When you invest in an IRA, 401(k) or other tax-deferred plan, you make a deal with Uncle Sam: You get years of tax-deferred growth, but you have to start taking money out--and give a cut to the IRS--after you turn age 70½. The calculations can be complicated, and the penalties for missteps are steep: If you don't take the required minimum distribution by the deadline each year, you'll pay a penalty of 50% of the amount you should have withdrawn. The prospect of taking RMDs and facing the tax bill can be daunting, but there are a number of strategies you can use to minimize taxes, make the most of your investments and avoid costly mistakes. SEE ALSO: 57 Dividend Stocks You Can Count On in 2019",IRS,en,Kiplinger
